    • onModifyCustomerButtonAction

      public void onModifyCustomerButtonAction(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Handles modify customer request. Checks that a customer has been selected. If so, it fetches that customer's information, launches the modify customer dialog, and pre-populates the fields with that information. If no customer has been selected, displays an error message instead prompting user to select a customer.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the modify customer button click event
      Throws:
      IOException - for input/output exceptions

    • onDeleteCustomerButtonAction

      public void onDeleteCustomerButtonAction()
      Handles delete customer request. Checks that a customer has been selected. If so, it fetches that customer's information and displays an alert with the customer's information, including the number of associated appointments, to confirm the user wants to delete. If user confirms, all of the customer's appointments are deleted first, and then the customer, to avoid database issues with the Customer_ID foreign key.

    • onModifyAppointmentButtonAction

      public void onModifyAppointmentButtonAction(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Handles modify appointment request. Checks that an appointment has been selected. If so, it fetches that appointment's information, launches the modify appointment dialog, and pre-populates the fields with that information. If no appointment has been selected, displays an error message instead prompting user to select an appointment.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the modify appointment button click event
      Throws:
      IOException - for input/output exceptions

    • onDeleteAppointmentButtonAction

      public void onDeleteAppointmentButtonAction()
      Handles delete appointment request. Checks that an appointment has been selected. If so, it fetches that appointment's information and displays an alert with the appointment's information, to confirm the user wants to delete. If user confirms, the appointment is deleted from the database.

    • onSignOutButtonAction

      public void onSignOutButtonAction(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Handles sign out request. Displays a confirmation dialog asking the user if they really want to sign out. If confirmed, the current (i.e., authenticated) user is reset to null and the login screen is shown. Otherwise the user is returned to the main screen.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the Sign Out button click event
      Throws:
      IOException
